Vibrational properties of C-Dots were analysed by Raman spectroscopy. It is expected that the Raman active carbonaceous materials show two characteristic main peaks, the so-called D and G-band, at around 1350 cm−1 and 1600 cm−1. The intensity of the D-band is thereby proportional to the amount of disordered sp3 carbon; and the intensity of the G-band proportional to the amount of ordered graphitic (sp2) carbon contained in the analysed sample. These two correlations represent a possibility to determine the graphitization degree of the synthesized samples by calculating relative intensity ratio of these two bands (IDIG)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
